race.comment: Tricky maiden to decipher, so I'll side with the unraced brigade. BIT TIRED ACTUALLY (5) comes through a good heat at Belmont. While she was beaten 4.7L there, the winner has run strong time and that looks to set her up nicely for her debut. The blinkers were on for that trial and they remain on for her race debut. Can make an impact right away. ROYAL GUARDIAN (9) looks well educated following a number of trials spanning the last 12 months. She did well to hang with them in a 400m heat at Belmont recently and that's her only trial this time in work. 1200m looks ideal fresh and she can put her best foot forward. I'LL KEEP HALF (8) was sound on debut at Albany and can improve on that performance. WRITTEN SIN (4) is next best dropping back a level.
